ShortName: Hypothesis tests, p-values & CIs
Concepts: Null vs alternative (the boring default vs "something's going on"), the test statistic as estimate ÷ SE (distance from the null in noise units), the p-value SIMULATED as "chance of a result this extreme if the null were true", reject/fail-to-reject at the 0.05 convention (one- vs two-sided), Type I/II error as false alarm vs missed signal, a confidence interval as estimate ± ~2·SE with "CI excludes the null $\iff$ $p<0.05$", and reading the Estimate/SE/statistic/p columns of any model table
BuildsOn: [randomness-samples-and-sampling-distributions](randomness-samples-and-sampling-distributions/lesson.qmd), [probability-and-odds](probability-and-odds/lesson.qmd)
UsedBy: —
